cs.DC, cs.DB, cs.OS, cs.DS, cs.CR

This paper is about building a scalable and highly available datastore, which is a topic that falls under several computer science sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) since the paper describes Spinnaker as a datastore designed to run on a large cluster of commodity servers in a single datacenter. The second likely category is cs.DB (Databases) since the paper describes Spinnaker's transactional get-put API and replication protocol. The third likely category is cs.OS (Operating Systems) since the paper discusses the design of a distributed system. The fourth likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) since the paper describes Spinnaker's key-based range partitioning. The fifth likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) since the paper mentions the use of Paxos to ensure consistency and availability.
